body:
@jtag and I were talking about writing a post that explains to agencies why they don't need to make an app (or maybe the rare case when it might be useful). We've all heard the idea a number of times: "Oh, we have to make an app. People love apps!" But I think we'd all agree that except on rare occasions, they're a terrible use of money and don't help users. 

Scratch pad with ideas that will eventually turn into the draft [lives here](https://docs.google.com/a/gsa.gov/document/d/1dsovOdj65zU3aXnp4mTZ9nDtL2xwfAQ4rWrA1fQpNNA/edit).

Please chime in with thoughts!
